This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction. Additionally, the use of word embeddings and positional embeddings further supports this categorization. 

The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques such as Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed model on a standard dataset, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

Finally, the paper involves the comparison of the proposed model with existing methods, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
